The Art of Mosaics
Lerner Publications | 1975 | 0822508281 | English | 104 pages | PDF | 23 MB

The art of mosaics had a long and colourful history in the ancient world. The first mosaics were made by prehistoric people who decorated the handles of their tools with small bits of coloured stone. In later periods, mosaic artists used new materials and new techniques to produce the graceful mosaic pavements of the Greek and Roman worlds
